==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Adularia
<hw>Ad`u*la"ri*a</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<ets>Adula</ets>, a mountain peak in Switzerland, where fine specimens
are found.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A transparent or translucent
variety of common feldspar, or orthoclase, which often shows pearly
opalescent reflections; -- called by lapidaries
<xex>moonstone</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Adulate</ent>⟦br⟧
